    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiScramblingCircuit[a, spec, ...] generate the Bravyi circuit (i.e., \
quantum circuits of fermionic Gaussian gates) realization of a(t) := \
u^\\[Dagger] (t) a u(t) for the study quantum information scrambling, where a \
is a local Bravyi unitary operator and u(t) is the time-evolution operator. \
For the remaining arguments spec, ..., see RandomBravyiCircuit. \
BravyiScramblingCircuit[k, spec, ...] assumes a := fk + f_k^\\[Dagger] on the \
k^th fermion mode.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
